topics.body:
You know I thought of something interesting when it comes to NASA; you know how there's fuck tons of ideological groups that have been trying to shut down science for fucking ages?  Like how NASA the past decade has constantly fucking dealed with people trying to defund them?

When you think about it there's a small number of people that legitimately don't want science to progress and don't want us to space travel for fear of finding out we're not the greatest thing every to be created in the universe.


I know this is dragging religion into it, but for example certain groups legitimately do believe that the *ENTIRE* universe solely exists for humans and when presented with information that there probably are a infinite number of other universes their reaction is "it's for humans too" even when you point out that there's probably a infinite number of universes and the number of universes is increasing infinitely and our universe is growing they legitimately believe that "god made all the universe and all universes solely for humans" and legitimately do not believe that there could ever be any alien life anywhere ever.


When you get down to it there's exists a niche of people that legitimately don't want any science to progress for fear of something negatively impacting their belief that they personally are the greatest thing to have ever existed and that they are metaphorically god's/gods' gift to everyone.
